text:
Keep sharing your pain, your frustration, your anger. Tell your lawmakers that enough is enough, that you’re not going to put up with anymore inaction on passing laws to end gun violence. 

If they don’t listen, vote them out.

Aurora.
Sandy Hook.
Charleston.
Orlando. 
Las Vegas. 
Sutherland Springs, TX.

After each of these communities were devastated by horrific acts of gun violence, what happened in Congress? Nothing. 

Enough is enough. Congress must act now.

The NRA and the gun industry just want to protect their profits—it is all about money and greed. They want to keep selling weapons of war to anyone willing to pay, no matter how unsafe it makes the rest of us. It has nothing to do with protecting the Second Amendment.

It’s not “too soon” to talk about solutions to end gun violence in this country. I reject that notion. The time to talk about them is now—today, tomorrow, and every day after, until we confront this epidemic.
Wishing peace, prosperity, and happiness to all celebrating the #LunarNewYear. Xinnián kuàilè! Saehae bok manhi badeuseyo!

Heartbreaking and horrific images from yet another school shooting, this time in Parkland, FL. ​Thinking of the victims and their families, and grateful to the first responders on the scene. When will enough be enough for Congress to finally take gun violence seriously?

Our country is better and stronger because of the contributions of our Dreamers. They deserve to know that their futures are secure. As this debate finally moves to the Senate floor, let’s give everything we can to the fight to protect them. #DreamActNow

Saranac Lake’s Chris @Mazdzer just made history by earning Team USA’s first ever medal for men’s singles luge at the Winter Olympics! Congratulations, you had us all at the edge of our seats! #BestofUS
The President has shown through words and actions that he doesn’t value women. It’s not surprising that he doesn’t believe survivors or understand the national conversation that is happening.
This is an important time to talk about this WH and whether they value women. Because, consistently, their actions tell us they don’t.

Senators on both sides of the aisle have a moral obligation to fight for Dreamers as hard as we'd fight for our own families. I have made clear, again and again, that I won’t vote for any long-term spending deal that does not protect them. The same goes for today’s vote.
We cannot continue to sit idly by and watch hundreds of thousands of Dreamers live in fear of deportation. They deserve justice now.
We should not have to make American workers choose between paid family leave and Social Security. That is a false choice, and it's wrong.

Our country desperately needs #paidleave, but we shouldn't rob Peter to pay Paul. Any plan that cuts into Social Security will hit low-income workers, seniors, and women the hardest. That's wrong. 

Congress should work to strengthen Social Security, and pass the #FAMILYAct.
Thank you @SenatorShaheen for signing on to the #FAMILYAct! Grateful to have your support as we fight to get #paidleave to every worker in this country.

Do you you have a story to tell about a time when you really needed #paidleave but didn’t have it? Or a time when you did have #paidleave, and it helped your family or your business? I'd love to know—tell me in a reply! #FMLA25

The #FAMILYAct would allow every American worker up to 12 weeks of #paidleave to care for a new child, a sick family member, or a personal medical emergency. The best part? Through shared responsibility, it’d cost workers and employers the price of a cup of coffee a week. #FMLA25
FMLA was an important step forward for our working families, but it doesn’t apply to 40 percent of the workforce. And it doesn’t guarantee any pay during the time that the worker is away. #FMLA25

25 years ago, the Family and Medical Leave Act was signed into law. It was an incredible step forward for millions of working families. Today, let’s renew our call for the next step forward: A national paid family and medical leave program. #FMLA25
More than 150 young women and girls have shown incredible courage by coming forward about the horrific abuse they suffered at the hands of Dr. Larry Nassar.

Dreamers across the country continue to wait for a permanent fix for DACA. Hundreds of thousands of young people are living in fear of what might happen to them. Let's do the right thing and give them the opportunity to keep contributing to our communities.

Today marks the beginning of #BlackHistoryMonth, a time to honor and celebrate the achievements of leaders, innovators, and trailblazers in the Black community; and a time to reflect upon the countless ways that they have shaped our nation.
If the president was really serious about creating a paid leave program that would help all workers, he would support my #FAMILYAct. Actions speak louder than words.
Thank you @SenTinaSmith for signing onto the #FAMILYAct and joining our call for a national paid leave program that will lift up all American families.

The president must address the crisis in Puerto Rico. We can't forget about our fellow citizens who still don't have access to basic resources. With Mayor @CarmenYulinCruz in the audience, I hope he and Republicans in Congress will be reminded of their responsibility. #SOTU

The president must address the lingering crisis of his own making: the status of our Dreamers who wait with uncertainty. He has the power to solve this right now. He should commit to helping them. Protecting our Dreamers is the right thing to do. #SOTU
The State of our Union should not be measured by the success of the stock market, and certainly not by tax cuts that overwhelmingly benefit corporations and CEOs. #SOTU
Tonight, the president must address how he will try to reward workers, not just the shareholders who are reaping the benefits of the economy at everyone else's expense. #SOTU
Tonight, the president must address how he will make higher education and vocational training more affordable and accessible so that our workers can get better paying jobs. #SOTU

Tonight, the president must address his plans to bring down the cost of health care for everyone who continues to struggle to afford it. This a top concern that I keep hearing about from families across New York. #SOTU

At today's hearing of the Environment and Public Works Committee, I called on @EPAScottPruitt explain what the EPA is doing to address both the clean up of the Hudson River, and the harmful levels of toxic PFOA and PFOS that have been found throughout New York State.
I voted against the 20-week abortion ban. This bill was nothing more than another attempt by Republicans in Congress to control women's personal health care decisions.
A woman’s health care decisions are between her and her doctor, not politicians in Washington.

Tonight’s abortion ban vote is yet another attempt by Republican leaders to attack women’s reproductive rights. Jam the phone lines, post those tweets, and spread the word. We must all speak out on this.

It is an honor to announce that Mayor @CarmenYulinCruz of San Juan, Puerto Rico will join me at the #SOTU. Throughout the crisis in Puerto Rico, Mayor Cruz has shown extraordinary leadership and fearless advocacy for her city.

When we see hate in our communities, when we hear hateful words, when we see someone bullying or attacking others, let’s all have the courage to say: “Not on our watch.” “Not in my community.” “Not here, not now.”

#WeRemember

If women made up 51% of Congress, do you think we would still be fighting to protect a woman’s right to choose? Do you think that the Senate would be voting on a dangerous 20-week abortion ban? 
 
Absolutely not.

Here we go again: Next week, the Senate will vote on legislation that would ban abortions after 20 weeks. This bill is unconstitutional and could have disastrous consequences for women and families across the country. We must all come together to stop it from passing.

Our fellow American citizens in Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands have been waiting for too long. The federal government has not done enough. We can’t let this slip. We can't let another funding bill go by without helping them.
Together, we must rise to the occasion and forge the political will to stand with the families of Puerto Rico until the islands are fully rebuilt. We need a new Marshall Plan to help them.

While the headlines have begun to recede, the humanitarian crisis in Puerto Rico remains as urgent as ever. Our fellow citizens continue to suffer. Many don’t have electricity or clean water to drink. Their hospitals don’t have enough supplies. Workers aren’t getting paid.
We must all hold the president and Republicans in Congress to their promises on Dreamers. Hundreds of thousands of young people are counting on us. Your voice is needed more than ever.

The shutdown is over, but we have not yet solved the moral crisis before us. Each day, hundreds of Dreamers lose their protections and live in fear of deportation. They deserve to know that their futures are secure in the only country they’ve ever called home.

Women should always have the right, freedom, and privacy to make their own decisions about their bodies, with their doctors and families—and without the federal government barging its way into the conversation. #7in10forRoe #Roe45

Roe v. Wade was one of the most consequential Supreme Court decisions for women’s rights in this country. As we look back on the progress made in the 45 years since, let’s continue to defend the right of every woman to be able to access the care she needs. #7in10forRoe #Roe45
I am deeply disappointed that today’s outcome fails to protect Dreamers. They deserve better from the elected leaders of the only country many of them have ever called home.
One year after the #WomensMarch, our grassroots energy is growing, not fading. It’s clearer than ever that women are holding our democracy together in these dangerous times.

One year ago, the day after President Trump was sworn into office, something extraordinary happened: We saw the rebirth of the women’s movement when thousands of women and men came together for the #WomensMarch, the single largest global protest in history.

Instead of protecting Dreamers, renewing health insurance for millions of children, and tackling the real problems hurting our families, the president and his enablers in Congress have manufactured a government shutdown.

For the first time in our nation’s history, we could have a government shutdown while one party controls the White House, the U.S. Senate, and the House of Representatives. A government shutdown is 100% avoidable.
Hundreds of thousands of Dreamers, young people who make enormous contributions to our communities, are counting on us to do the right thing. The clock is ticking. #DreamActNow

Early this year, the Senate plans to bring to the floor a bill intended to rollback Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform. I plan to oppose it. 

This bill puts limits on important oversight that would protect taxpayers from being on the hook for another bank bailout.
Protecting Dreamers is a moral imperative. I will not vote for a spending bill that doesn’t treat Dreamers fairly.

The Senate Finance Committee just voted to confirm Alex Azar, a former big pharma exec with a history of raising prescription drug prices, for HHS Secretary. Let's not let the fox guard the hen house. I will certainly #SayNotoAzar when he comes before the full Senate for a vote.

In New York State, Community Health Centers serve over 2 million people in low income and underserved communities. If Congress does not act quickly to reauthorize their funding, we could have a crisis on our hands.
Your reminder that nearly 9 million children and their families have waited for over 100 days for Congress to save the Children’s Health Insurance Program.

Some great news: We need just one more vote, from one more Senator, to have enough votes to reverse the Trump administration’s #NetNeutrality repeal. Keeping our internet free and open to everyone could not be more important. Contact your Senators today!

As we celebrate the remarkable legacy, work, and sacrifice of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr., we recognize the progress our country has made in the last 50 years. And in a year that has tested our resolve, we're reminded of the work still left to be done. #MLKDay

While we’ve seen remarkable outcomes in light of the #MeToo movement, we must keep pushing for the changes needed to make accountability possible for all women, no matter what industry they work in or the type of work they do. Everyone should feel safe to come forward.

This is incredible: In California, the activists behind @RecallPersky gathered 100,000 signatures to recall the judge who sentenced Brock Turner to just six months in jail after he was convicted of sexually assaulting an unconscious woman outside a frat party.
Our country’s diversity is a strength. Our history and heritage of immigration have always helped us thrive. These truths cannot, and will not, be diminished by hateful, racist words.

We won't let the president's hateful words define us, nor will we let our compassion fade. Let's stand in unity with the brave people of Haiti, who were devastated by a tragic earthquake 8 years ago. The strength they've shown in the face of tragedy is inspiring.

Iranians should have every right to raise their voices in protest without fear of intimidation or violence from their government. I've joined my colleagues @SenBobCorker, @SenatorCardin on a Senate resolution to affirm that right.
Congratulations to @shelley4senate on winning the Democratic nomination for New York State Senate District 37. I look forward to supporting your campaign!
To all Dreamers: You are part of our communities, you are part of the fabric of this country, and you deserve to be part of our future. We will not stop fighting for you. #DreamActNow

I am deeply troubled by the reports that President Trump personally interviewed Geoffrey Berman to permanently fill the post of Manhattan U.S. attorney, and find it disqualifying, considering the potential conflicts of interest on matters that could affect the president himself.
It has been over 100 days since funding expired for the Children’s Health Insurance Program. Have you taken action this week and called on Congress to renew coverage for nearly 9 million children?

Dreamers shouldn't be used as political pawns to pay for an absurd border wall. We shouldn't put hundreds of thousands of lives on the line just so that the president can fulfill a hateful campaign promise. It's nonsense. We need to pass a clean #DreamActNow.

If President Trump really wants to rebuild our crumbling infrastructure, he should start by working constructively with Democrats and Republicans from New York and New Jersey on the Gateway Project, the single most important rail project in the country.
Passing adequate, long-term funding for the Children’s Health Insurance Program shouldn’t be a partisan issue. Let’s get to work.
Another week has passed and Congress has done nothing to help the hundreds of thousands of Dreamers who are living in fear of losing their status and are at risk of deportation.

Our country is in the midst of an opioid crisis and the AG is going to divert resources to cracking down on medical marijuana? This is either willfully ignorant or cowing to corporate greed on behalf of pharma special interest profits.

It has been over 100 days since Hurricane Maria made landfall in Puerto Rico. Over a million of our fellow citizens remain in crisis, and Congress has yet to give them the aid they need. Please, keep up the pressure and tell your members of Congress to take action now.

Nearly 9 million children across the country are waiting desperately for Congress to pass adequate, long-term funding for the Children’s Health Insurance Program. We cannot leave this unresolved any longer.

As of today, over 14,000 DACA recipients have lost their protections and face the risk of deportation. There are no more excuses. Protecting Dreamers and passing a clean #DreamActNow must be one of Congress’s top priorities this month.
We have big and important fights to wage together this year. Stay focused, stay hopeful, and please keep raising your voice. Thank you for all that you do. Happy New Year!

I’m so grateful for everyone who’s gotten off the sidelines, raised their voices, and fought for what we believe in this year. As you think ahead to 2018, I’d love for you to share some resolutions in a reply. Wishing you and your family a joyful, safe evening!

Here is your reminder that our fellow American citizens in Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands have suffered through the holidays without power, water, or refrigeration. They cannot wait any longer—Congress must act quickly to give them the funding needed to rebuild.

Securing adequate, long-term funding for the Children’s Health Insurance Program continues to be a major piece of unfinished business for this Congress. Millions of children across the country are counting on us to save their health coverage as soon as we are back in session.

I’m heartbroken at the news of the devastating fire in the Bronx last night. Praying for the New Yorkers we lost, for those still fighting for their lives, and for the families affected by this horrific tragedy. Thank you to @FDNY and first responders for your bravery.

As we look ahead to some very important fights in the new year, never forget that your voice matters. You never know: Your words and your actions can spark, shape, or lead an important debate. Keep showing up, keep speaking out, continue to be part of the conversation.

Allowing thousands of Dreamers to lose their protections and face the risk of deportation is not just immoral, it also hurts our economy and our communities. We cannot sit idly by. It's time for a clean #DreamActNow.
I voted no on the short-term CR. It did nothing to protect #Dreamers and did not fully reauthorize #CHIP. That’s unacceptable.

We cannot forget about the American families in Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands that have been without food, water, or electricity for over 12 weeks. They deserve nothing less than a fully funded Marshall Plan to rebuild.

Congress shouldn't turn a blind eye to Dreamers. If a member of your family was at risk, waiting until next month for Congress to act wouldn't be good enough. We should all fight for our Dreamers as hard as we'd fight for our own family members. #DreamActNow

Senate Republicans are doing nothing to address the fact that millions of children are only weeks or months away from losing #CHIP coverage. It’s shameful to lavish tax giveaways on wealthy donors while claiming children’s access to the most basic medical care is too expensive.

Across the country, Dreamers are living in fear of losing their jobs, of having to go into hiding, of having to make a choice between staying here undocumented or being forced out of the only country they've ever called home. #DreamActNow

The House’s disaster aid package does not do enough to help with the humanitarian crisis in Puerto Rico—and it doesn’t address the debt crisis that has made Puerto Rico’s recovery harder than it needs to be.
In 2018, I hope you will channel your anger and energy into defeating those who voted to put their donors before hardworking middle-class families.
Taking decisive action to protect Dreamers is a matter of basic human rights and dignity—it's about people’s lives. #DreamActNow

Soon, the Senate will vote on a damaging bill that gives tax cuts to corporations at expense of middle class families, & sets the stage for cuts to Medicare, Medicaid, & Social Security. This bill is Washington's culture of soft corruption at its absolute worst—I'm voting NO.

The Republican tax plan is an abomination—nothing but a massive giveaway to corporations and the wealthiest Americans. Time is running out before the final vote on this plan, so please make sure to keep up the pressure. Contact your Senators and tell them to vote NO.

For each day that Congress fails to act to protect Dreamers, 122 DACA recipients lose their status and face the risk of deportation. 

It is Congress' moral obligation to take decisive action. #cleanDreamActNow

This week, my Republican colleagues are eager to send an early holiday present to their corporate donors through the #GOPTaxScam.

If you're part of a middle class family, it's very likely that you'll take a hit. Keep speaking out.

In the name of handouts to corporations and the wealthiest Americans, the #GOPTaxScam

• blows a hole in our deficit
• raises the cost of health insurance 
• could raise taxes on the middle class 
• could make drastic cuts to Medicare and Social Security
The real winners from the #GOPTaxScam will be the corporate shareholders, CEOs, and lobbyists that were paid to write the bill.
Republicans are rushing to pass their disaster of a tax bill, so please keep up the calls, tweets, letters, emails. We need your voice now more than ever.

We still need your voice in the fight against the GOP tax plan. 

Why? It'll kick millions off of health insurance. It's likely to raise middle class taxes—and it could lead to drastic cuts to Medicaid & Social Security, all to repay the GOP's corporate donors.

As of today, over 12,000 DACA recipients have lost their status. This is shameful. 

Let’s get to work to pass the #DreamActNow.

5 years ago today, 20 kids and 6 educators were killed at Sandy Hook Elementary. My heart goes out to all whose lives were torn apart by gun violence on December 14, 2012, and on every day since. Congress’ failure to act is shameful. We need to pass lifesaving reform now.

Today, the @FCC is voting on a proposal to wipe out #NetNeutrality, which ensures that the Internet is free, fair, and open to the millions of people who use it every day. Keep fighting back—make yourself heard on this.

Ten years ago, @TaranaBurke created the #MeToo movement to tell young women of color who had survived sexual assault that they were not alone. This sparked a powerful movement, made uniquely possible by a free and open internet. 
 
This is why we must fight for #NetNeutrality.
Republicans should not rush to pass their terrible tax plan until @GDouglasJones is seated in the Senate.
Congrats, @GDouglasJones, on your win in Alabama! This is a victory for showing up, fighting to the end, and standing for what’s right.
Women are a force to be reckoned with. We won’t be silenced.
Wishing a very happy, joyful, and bright #Hanukkah to all those who are celebrating!
President Trump should resign. But, of course, he won't hold himself accountable. Therefore, Congress should investigate the multiple sexual harassment and assault allegations against him.

Republicans in the House and the Senate are cutting backroom deals in a rush to pass their massive corporate tax cuts into law, which could amount to a complete disaster for middle class families. We must keep fighting back against this bill.
When it comes to sexual assault, harassment, and the general mistreatment of women, we must be able to call out anyone, Democrat or Republican.

Today, we remember the heroes who lost their lives at #PearlHarbor 76 years ago, and all who lost their lives in the war that followed. We honor the families who carry with them the memories of those they lost. May God bless them and all who serve in our Armed Forces.
Families across the country who rely on #CHIP are needlessly living with the fear that their children might lose health insurance, all because Congress has yet to act. This is troubling.

The Senate and the House still must come together to vote on a final tax bill. We must keep spreading the word about just how devastating this would be for America's middle class. Whether by call, text, or tweet, keep doing what you can to stop this bill from becoming law.
I encourage you to keep raising your voices. Your stories matter. We will listen. We will believe you.

As elected officials, we should be held to the highest standards—not the lowest. The allegations against Sen. Franken describe behavior that cannot be tolerated. While he’s entitled to an Ethics Committee hearing, I believe he should step aside to let someone else serve.
It's a complete travesty that #Dreamers must be forced to wait and see if our Republican-controlled Congress has the guts to stand up to the president and do what’s right and humane.

Republicans left some big items to address as they focused on cutting corporate taxes last week: 

• Government funding, which runs out on Friday
• The uncertain futures of hundreds of thousands Dreamers
• Renewing CHIP for almost 9 mil kids

Can I count on you to speak out?

In the middle of the night, Republicans rammed through their atrocious tax scam. We didn’t have time to read the nearly 500 pages of partially handwritten, scribbled notes—unlike the lobbyists who knew what was in the bill before we did.
Heading to the Senate floor to vote NO on the Republican tax plan. Huge corporations don’t need any extra help. They’ll be just fine.

I want to note that we’ve barely had time to review the revised Republican tax plan—and we might be voting on it as soon as TONIGHT. It is astounding the lengths that Republicans will go for corporate tax cuts.

Flynn news is a BIG deal, but please also pay close attention to the Senate floor. Sen. McConnell just said he has the votes for the tax scam bill. Keep the pressure on—call your Senators and tell them to vote NO!
Republicans have been rewriting this horrible tax plan behind closed doors, but they're still keen to rush a vote on it today. How reckless. I hope you’ve been making those calls.

We won’t be voting on the tax bill tonight, so keep making those calls and posting those tweets! Make sure your Senators hear from you about how this horrible tax plan could affect you or your family, then tell them to vote NO.

The Senate will be voting on the harmful Republican tax plan without the much-needed debate, oversight, and transparency it should have. I’m voting against it and I need you with me. Be heard today—do everything you can to speak out and oppose this plan.

A good tax system should do three things: It should reward work. It should be fair for working families. It should help create good-paying jobs. 

The Republican tax plan does none of that.

Let’s be clear about what the Republican tax plan really is: It is Washington corruption at its peak—nothing more than paying back donors through corporate welfare, at the expense of the middle class.
The harmful Republican tax plan could come to a vote as soon as this week. You know what to do—speak out against it. It’s as easy as a quick phone call to Congress: (202) 224-3121
Here’s how we make change: Put more women in leadership, from the U.S. military, to boardrooms, to Congress.
Sexual harassment is not confined to any one industry or any one person, it’s prevalent across society—and it’s our obligation to confront it, change the climate, and hold people accountable.

Small businesses are deeply important to our communities in New York State and across the country. I hope you'll support them and #ShopSmall today! 

Will you tell me how you're celebrating #SmallBizSat?

It has been nearly two months since Congress let health insurance coverage expire for almost 9 million children. That is cruel and absurd. I hope you’ll call on your representatives to reauthorize CHIP as soon as possible.
#NetNeutrality is good for our economy and vital to our freedom of speech. I urge you to raise your voice on this. Do not let the FCC take away a free and open internet.

I’m hearing from families in every corner of my state who are already struggling just to stay afloat. If the Republican tax plan passes, there's a good chance they will take a big hit. We must defeat this awful bill.
The FCC is siding with big corporations by releasing a plan to claw back #NetNeutrality rules. They were hoping you wouldn’t notice. We must fight back to defend a free and open internet.

A reminder: Senate Republicans are trying to pass a tax bill that will leave millions of Americans uninsured and raise insurance prices, all so that they can slash taxes for billionaires and big corporations. 

It’s up to all of us to speak out and stop it.

The allegations against Sen. Franken are deeply concerning. This kind of behavior is unacceptable and should not be tolerated anywhere in our society. There is nothing funny about it and there is no excuse for it. The Ethics Committee deserves answers from him.
In recent months, scandal after scandal has made clear that sexual assault and harassment remain pervasive in our military.
Completely unconscionable that Republicans want to kick 13 million off of health insurance in the name of tax cuts for corporations and the wealthiest Americans.

Because of you, we defeated Trumpcare three times. It is absolutely critical to do the same for the harmful Republican tax plan. Please, take the time to contact your elected officials this week on this issue. Be heard.
We should be rewarding work in this country, not doling out lavish tax cuts to big businesses, CEOs, and bankers.
I cannot say this clearly enough: If you're not rich—if you’re part of a hard working, middle class family—then there’s a good chance you'll take a hit if the Republican tax plan passes.
A very happy birthday to the U.S. Marine Corps! Thank you to every Marine who has served and who continues to serve.
Four women all with shocking stories. I believe them.
If you thought the House tax plan was bad, the Senate plan is worse. This is corporate welfare at the expense of the middle class.
The Republican tax plan is a blatant attempt to hand the collective wealth and resources of our country to rich corporations on the Fortune 500 list.

To the voters who made themselves heard last night: Our victories across the country belong to you—and we're just getting started. Next year, let’s build on this momentum to take back the House and Senate.
Plain and simple, Americans are being slaughtered and Congress is refusing to stand up for them. This is a monumental failure of leadership.
I reject the notion that it is “too soon” to act on gun violence. If not now, when? We cannot wait any longer.
#ElectionDay is Tuesday! I’m thrilled to support many great New York Democrats up and down the ballot & I'd like to share a bit about them.
I’ll sum up the new Republican tax plan: The super-rich and big corporations get kickbacks, middle class Americans are left in the dust.
Years of corporate donations are paying off today as House Republicans unveil their new tax plan.
New Yorkers are resilient. No cowardly act of terror can change who we are.
As NYC has shown over and over, we are resilient. We will not cower to senseless hate. I am confident we will get answers.
A horrific act of terror in NYC today. My heart is with the victims and families—I am grateful to the NYPD, FDNY, EMS, NYS police and FBI.
5 years since #Sandy hit communities across NY, we must recognize the work left to do to help our families still struggling to recover.
I can't wait to take the stage at the #WomensConvention tonight. Are you attending or watching? If so, tell me what you're excited about!
Any plan to end the opioid epidemic must include ending the over-prescription of these medications for acute pain.
Dreamers are leaders, teachers, innovators, and scientists. We must do what we can to give them a path to citizenship.
I voted for the Disaster Relief funding bill, but I want to be clear that it is not enough to help with Puerto Rico & USVI's recovery.
The Senate GOP is calling a vote on a bill to make it easier for corporations to use forced arbitration—a practice that harms consumers.
Did you know that big corporations can get massive tax deductions for paying excessively high salaries to their CEOs?
Happy #SpiritDay—today and everyday, let’s show our support for #LGBTQ youth and stand together against all forms of bullying.
Wishing a joyful and happy #Diwali to all celebrating the Festival of Lights in New York and around the world!
I'm proud to join @PattyMurray, @LouiseSlaughter, @RepDianaDeGette on a bill to reverse Pres. Trump's rollback of the birth control mandate.
If you’re a member of Congress and not even willing to renew health insurance funding for vulnerable children, then who are you serving?
Let's be clear: The Senate GOP budget is a vehicle to a huge tax cut for big corporations & the rich, written by big corporations & the rich
As Tom Marino withdraws his nomination to be drug czar, perhaps the president should stop nominating industry shills altogether.
To survivors who have shown extraordinary courage by speaking up: You're not alone. We're listening. And we believe you.
Congress must still take up the unfinished business of renewing health insurance for 9 million children. Have you made your voice heard yet?
The president’s decision to end ACA subsidies is a cruel attempt to play partisan politics with our health care.
In 2017, no boss should get to decide a woman’s access to birth control. I’m sick of these relentless attempts to roll back our progress.
It would serve the Trump administration well to quickly embrace the fact that climate change is real―our safety and security depend on it.
A woman’s health care decisions should be made between her and her doctor. No one else.
The House has voted to attack women's reproductive rights once again. It's a horrific piece of legislation.
Ending DACA doesn’t make our country safer or our economy stronger. I hope you’ll lead where the president won’t and stand up for Dreamers.
Congress must take gun violence as seriously as the threat of terrorism. If you agree, call your representatives today.
Devastated to hear of the horrific tragedy in Las Vegas. My heart is with the victims and families. Grateful to the responders at the scene.
CHIP expires tonight. Congress must act—join me in fighting for coverage for 9 million kids. This should be a no brainer.
I will vote against @AjitPaiFCC. We must protect net neutrality rules on behalf of freedom of speech and innovation.
Trump's tax plan helps large profitable corporations and millionaires, shortchanges lower income workers and the middle class. A cruel joke.
Today was a victory in our fight to save health care for millions. But remember this: The fight won't end until we flip the House & Senate.
Thank you. Your calls, letters, tweets, and actions helped to stop the health care vote. Never underestimate the power of your voice.
It is clear that millions of Americans would be harmed by #GrahamCassidy. This bill would hurt many families.
Checking in: Have you called your Senators this morning to help protect health care for millions of Americans?
This fight still isn't over—please keep up the calls to stop the #GrahamCassidy bill once and for all.
It’s time to pass the #DREAMAct for the 800,000 young people who know only the United States as their home.
L'Shanah Tovah to all celebrating Rosh Hashanah. Sending my warmest wishes for a happy New Year.
#GrahamCassidy is yet another health care repeal bill that will kick millions off of coverage.
